<item>
            <title>[LU-7178] possible invalid memset in osd_acct_index_lookup</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7178</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The memset above look invalid.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; osd_acct_index_lookup(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; struct lu_env *env,
                 struct dt_object *dtobj,
                 struct dt_rec *dtrec,
                 &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; struct dt_key *dtkey)
{
    struct osd_thread_info  *info = osd_oti_get(env);
#ifdef HAVE_DQUOT_FS_DISK_QUOTA
    struct fs_disk_quota    *dqblk = &amp;amp;info-&amp;gt;oti_fdq;
#&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt;
    struct if_dqblk     *dqblk = &amp;amp;info-&amp;gt;oti_dqblk;
#endif
    struct super_block  *sb = osd_sb(osd_obj2dev(osd_dt_obj(dtobj)));
    struct lquota_acct_rec  *rec = (struct lquota_acct_rec *)dtrec;
    __u64            id = *((__u64 *)dtkey);
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;          rc;
#ifdef HAVE_DQUOT_KQID
    struct kqid     qid;
#endif

    ENTRY;

    memset((void *)dqblk, 0, sizeof(struct obd_dqblk));
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Shouldn&apos;t that be ?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;memset(dqblk, 0, sizeof(*dqblk));
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;or am I missing some subtlety?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If it&apos;s a bug it&apos;s also probably not seen by the static analyser because of the unneeded void * cast.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
